cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "potpourri: Multi-period Optimal Power Flow for Distribution Grids"
message: >-
  If you use this software, please cite it using the metadata in this file.
type: software
license: MIT
version: "0.2.1"
date-released: "2026-04-24"   # update to the date of the tagged release
repository-code: "https://github.com/RWTH-IAEW/opf-potpourri"
url: "https://github.com/RWTH-IAEW/opf-potpourri"
abstract: >-
  potpourri is a Python library for multi-period Optimal Power Flow (OPF) in
  distribution grids. It wraps Pyomo for optimisation modelling over
  pandapower network objects, supporting AC/DC power-flow formulations and
  flexible resources such as batteries, electric vehicles, heat pumps,
  photovoltaic systems, and wind generators.
keywords:
  - optimal power flow
  - distribution grid
  - power systems
  - multi-period
  - pyomo
  - pandapower
  - simbench
  - battery storage
  - hosting capacity
